 valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Focus items</span><hr size=1> I honestly think that Verant is going to little if not nothing to our current pet damage output (Except the 50+ Fire pets, they need some tweaking no matter how you look at it). But this doesn't mean the pets don't need upgrades. I think our best avenue of getting these upgrades without upsetting their precious non-existent balance would be to give us high end focus items. I know this has been presented before as a passing thought in some threads, but I believe it's our best shot.<br>
<br>
I'll start with factors that must be limited. If they give us an item that will up pet str, atk, agi, dex by +150 (and yes, I think it's reasonable, read on) it MUST be zone limited. Anything that turns out pets into larger lawnmowers than they already are, it's going to offset group experiencing. While I do believe some lesser focus items should be usable in all zones, we need a few that dramatically increase pet power against uber mobs.<br>
<br>
For Verants sake, let's say we only do five items (I believe there should be more, but quite frankly, we make up a small percent of the customer base, they are NOT going to do anything time/code intensive for us, live with it) one for each kind of pet (include RoZ = 5).<br>
<br>
These items drop off raid caliber mobs and increase not only pet stats, but increase pet level by at least 2, possibly up to 5 for best of the best focus. These are all nodrop, so they don't even have to worry about a lvl 10 Mage running around with a focus item dropped off the Creator.<br>
<br>
I don't have any numbers as to pet stat increases because I honestly don't have any clue as to there starting stats (other than hp), if anyone wants to post some thoughts on numbers feel free. <br>
<br>
Let me know what you think of this guys, I honestly believe this is our best avenue of increasing the pets damage in the endgame.<br>
<br>
 <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=34808>Aidonis</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/useek9.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seek 9</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 506<br> <font color=#333333>(3/13/02 4:50:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=133.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Focus items</span><hr size=1> I don't care for it simply because a warrior, with an insane uber-sword, can use that weapon in any zone he/she likes, whether it is ToV or Crushbone, and do the same level of uber damage.  The same goes for all their armor and other items.  They work <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> everwhere.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->   Right?<br>
<br>
Why do you feel that we must be limited in such a way when no other class loses thier prime damage-dealing tools by being &quot;zone-dependent.&quot;<br>
<br>
If you want to limit something, then make it level based or time based, not zone.  Warriors has time limits on the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> defensive</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> skill.   There are damage caps on weapons due to the wielder's <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> level</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.   While these caps should be looked at and made more reasonable, a level cap on a focus item also can make sense.  In fact, the Sol Ro Focus items are &quot;capped&quot; since they will not affect any post-50 pets.  Likewise, the Elemental Mastery staves affect level 49 to 60 pets.<br>
<br>
The focus effects as they currently exist today are quite marginal from what I have seen, especially for the Elemental Mastery staves.   These items might be seriously reworked.   Also, there is nothing against them scaling with the level of the Mage, generating a greater focus-effect that is a function of the level of the Mage. Why not?  Should not a level 60 Mage be able to summon and focus a pet that is superior to a level 51 Mage when they both cast Vocerate Earth and both have the Earth Staff?<br>
IMHO, lets not sell ourselves short.<br>
 <p><b>Seek Pyremaker</b><br>
Mage 52nd Season, Spec-Evocation, Xegony<br>
Proud member of "The Ring of Truth"
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ud5aidan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>D5 AidaN</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#333333>(3/13/02 5:12:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=133.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Focus items</span><hr size=1> Why? Because if we get a focus item that dramatically increases our pets dmg output, it will mess up xp groups. If that happens, it's not getting implemented, period. Also remember that we should be getting a few spells, that will be usable anywhere.<br>
<br>
Simply put we have &quot;penalties&quot; that melee's don't because we have spells that can do massive amounts of damage very fast. Quite frankly any focus WILL have to be limited in some way shape or form.<br>
<br>
A level restriction is prolly the best bet, but something that &quot;scales&quot; in power would be great and all, but i don't see them putting in the time to do it for us. Remeber we have to be realistic about this guys. <br>
<br>
We are the least played Caster class, and I guarantee we're the last class that gets its balancing done on test. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=34808>Aidonis</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukinelaria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kinelaria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#333333>(3/13/02 12:16:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=133.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Focus items</span><hr size=1>    Boy, you've really let them beat you down. Of course we should be powerful, we're casters. We can do alot of damage quickly, yes, but it's not without a cost. It takes mana to make a pet, albeit this can be a one time only cost, and it takes mana to nuke. You only get so much mana to use and then have to wait for it to come back. For this power we sacrifice combat skills, good armor to protect us, and hitpoints. Melee on the other hand gets damage that is more or less  free, can hit anything without worrying whether his blows will land (unless of course it's a red mob, but we're talking xp groups I believe). As for having a stronger pet helping a group kill faster, I fail to see the problem. I doubt it could steal xp from a full group, and if solo'ing or duo'ing you might find that even sharing xp with the pet your rate of killing is higher and your net gains are still better (and if not, you can just simply not focus the pet), though hopefully they'll remove that inane xp penalty, like pet's need xp.<br>
<br>
Kinelaria J`Nes<br>
Taeru<br>
Lana J`Nes<br>
