Innoruuk Server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=zeem>Zeem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 162<br> <font color=#333333>(3/13/02 12:54:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=133.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Well..</span><hr size=1> Ofcourse we do alot of dmg ...  We should, have you looked at your HP lately, have you every wondered why your AC usually half of a ranger?<br>
<br>
This is because we are casters, 3 of the casting classes are about doing dmg.<br>
<br>
<br>
We have no crowdcontrol spells, we have no ports, we have no heal, we have few buffs. In short we have very very little to offer a group, except ONE thing, damage.<br>
<br>
All dmgdealing classes should be treated equal, we should be able to outdmg any melee with a good margin, thats why we pay a HP/AC penalty compared to melee.<br>
Our pets SHOULD be as powerfull as most melee, it is afterall a spell we use to do dmg, today this aint the case a Rogue outdmg a epicpet 5x on an ubermob, and against mobs with 300k hp pet + mage gets outdmged easy 2x-3x by a rogue, together we usually can't keep up with the MT thats on defensive and using taunting weapons over his best dmg once.<br>
<br>
Mages need to scale up alot in dmg, especially our pets.<br>
<br>
I don't care if our nukes get much upgraded, I am a mage, I like doing dmg with my pet. Today I don't use my pet on raids, simply because the dmg it does it not really worth having one up. If on the other hand my pets dmg was as good as any melee I would use it, despite bad pathing etc etc, I know how to control my pet, I know how to avoid getting trains from my pet (ususally involve runing away from group and die) and if the dmg my pet would make would make a diffrence (and why not be a must to succed a raid because of their almost immunity to certain spells) I would find ways to use it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showPrevMessage?topicID=133.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showNextMessage?topicID=133.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=133.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.threadControl?topicID=133.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=133.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=133.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method